The paper deals with the detection of cyber attacks in a connected vehicle environment using statistical models. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques such as Expectation Maximization (EM) and Cumulative Summation (CUSUM) algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also deals with real-time anomaly detection, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY) research. Finally, the paper uses simulation to generate data, which is a common technique in networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) research.
